Adding react-native-rating-element in list

I created an open source library for setting up "Rating System" in your mobile app. 
It supports:
decimal point ratings, direction aware like bottom to top or RTL etc, custom icons and images and record ratings given by user.

[react-native-rating-element](https://github.com/ui-ninja/react-native-rating-element)

Thank you 🙏🏻

React Native vs Flutter comparison article

We've written an article comparing Flutter and React Native to help folks think through which approach fits them best when building a mobile app.  The article suggests what approach may be best depending you the project requirements and experience level. https://buttercms.com/blog/flutter-vs-react-native-choosing-your-approach.

Add react-native-anchor-point. Currently, there is not public API in react-native providing the ability to set transformOrigin.  I made this function. It might look small, but actually it is very powerful.  With it, you can use the transform API in react-native to achieve many fancy animations.
